Package: tmfs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, fuse
Description: Time Machine File System
 Time Machine File System is a read-only virtual filesystem
 which helps you to read you Apple Time Machine Backup by
 reconstructing the hard-linked directories from the HFS+
 metadata directory.
 .
 You can browse the fuse-mounted tmfs Time Machine normally
 and recover data from any backup point contained within.
